                        <h1>Types Of Tooth Stains</h1>
                        <p>There are two basic types:</p>
                        <p><strong>Intrinsic Stains</strong> &ndash; stains that form on the interior of the teeth and occur by anything (and everything) from trauma to aging to mineral exposure to fluoride ingestion.</p>
                        <p><strong>Extrinsic Stains</strong> &ndash; the stains we can see on the exterior of the tooth. Certain extrinsic stains can become ingrained with the dentin if not dealt with soon.</p>
